<br>
I'd like to see a pet who casts 60th level cleric buffs on other pets and does resistances and heals (not a lot, I'm not asking for a ch or those tick heal spells, but something reasonable, a 400hp heal) other pets. A cleric pet that doesn't attack, just casts force strike and heals.<br>
<br>
I think it would be a great pet for duo mages or groups with &gt;2 pet classes. And on a raid it would actually do the upkeep of all the pets on the raid. A complete non-soloing pet that turns out little to no damage so that other pet classes can concentrate on other things.<br>
<br>
It is inherently balanced since it only deals with pets (except for the heal, which would need to be tested) and does not create the chance of doing anything that couldn't be done before. Also it creates the cool situation of pets actually taking care of their own on raids.<br>
<br>
I played around with the other classes, but none of them seem to work, except for possibly shaman, which would turn out to be a more powerful version of the one I described (and a slow would break it, so I dismiss that out of hand) because they buff better. Maybe a level 60 spell: Sylia's Spiritual Servant. Perhaps a calm water or air elemental look to them.<br>
<br>
Just spitting out a thought.<br>
<br>
Deelit Elementalcaller<br>
60 Arch Magi<br>
